#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Corrupted, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:5
msgid "Corrupted"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Corrupted, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Even among the Lightborns, the Corrupted are rarely seen in Blackqvasten and "
"the realms of the depths. While a Corrupted maintains some of her nature as a"
" faerie, the presence of Shassagoth has distorted and empowered it with "
"darkness. As a result, the Corrupted has access to high forms of destructive "
"magic that allow her to pull enemies directly into Shassagoth’s shadow "
"realms, where they are slowly consumed by the darkness.\n"
"\n"
"This unit is able to pull enemy units into the world of Shassagoth. Those "
"units will receive an additional +20% damage until the end of the turn."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:49
msgid "corrupt touch"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=secret, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:63
msgid "nether grip"
msgstr ""

#. [ethergrip]
#. [unstore_unit]
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:73
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:174
msgid "ether grip"
msgstr ""

#. [ethergrip]
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:74
msgid ""
"When a unit is hit with the ether grip weapon special, it will receive +20% "
"damage until the end of the turn."
msgstr ""

#. [unstore_unit]
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Corrupted.cfg:175
msgid "female^ether grip"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Harbinger, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Harbinger.cfg:5
msgid "Harbinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Harbinger, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Harbinger.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The Harbinger is the leader of the Deep Elves and an earthly representation "
"of Shassagoth. She is rarely seen, but wherever a Harbinger does appear, it "
"can be certain that war is imminent. Those who have witnessed her sorcery "
"firsthand have described it as a line of destruction, capable of devouring "
"everything in its path and leaving nothing but blood and death. It believed "
"that the Harbinger channels the energies of Shassagoth himself, providing her"
" a potent means to further spread the influence of the darkness. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Harbinger.cfg:40
msgid "nether touch"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Harbinger.cfg:49
msgid "twilight wave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Seeker, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Seeker.cfg:5
msgid "Blood Seeker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Seeker, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Seeker.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Whoever has incurred the hatred of the ghostly apparition that is the Seeker "
"will find death. Seekers are said to be able freely traverse through walls, "
"relentlessly pursing their marked quarries. The hunted prey is plagued with "
"nightmares of its own death until the Seeker’s blade transforms its visions "
"into reality. It is said that the Seeker’s sword consumes the souls of its "
"marks, imprisoning them within a cage of cold steel. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Seeker.cfg:50
msgid "blade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_dep_deep_wisp, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp.cfg:5
msgid "Wisp"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_dep_deep_wisp, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A wisp is a flickering light with magical capabilities. These mysterious "
"entities roam the caverns of Blackqvasten, usually wandering alone in the "
"endless darkness. Generally, wisps are not dangerous, even to beings that do "
"not inhabit the depths, although they are known to produce magic of "
"extraordinary power when gathered in large enough numbers. Legends say that "
"the Wiss are nothing more than lost souls, tortured by Shassagoth to wander "
"through the depths on unending journies to find peace. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp.cfg:33
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp_Greater.cfg:34
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp_Mother.cfg:39
msgid "orb"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_dep_deep_greater_wisp, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp_Greater.cfg:5
msgid "Greater Wisp"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_dep_deep_greater_wisp, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp_Greater.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Sometimes, one may find Wisps gathered in clusters in the depths. In their "
"midst, there appear a few larger wisps that are stronger than their smaller "
"kin. These Greater Wisps have the potential to cast lower forms of magic and "
"are more durable than the smaller Wisps. It is unknown how these Greater "
"Wisps came to be, but the strange light that they emanate attracts nearby "
"wisps, whereupon more Greater Wisps will eventually be found when the Wisps "
"begin to cluster. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Wisp_Mother, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp_Mother.cfg:4
msgid "Wisp Mother"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_deep_Wisp_Mother, race=AE_dep_deep_elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp_Mother.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Wispmothers are rare beings that glow with mysterious, eerie energy that "
"simultaneously appears as light, but also melds with the darkness. Often they"
" are surrounded by many Wisps and Greater Wisps, who are attracted and "
"empowered by the energy that the Wispmothers emit. The Wispmother, in turn, "
"controls the lesser Wisps like the queen of a hive, directing them with "
"unknown purpose. It is rumored that Wispmothers are not related to the "
"ordinary Deep Elves, but are instead the manifested thoughts of Shassagoth, "
"guiding the magical Wisps to do his bidding."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves\Wisp_Mother.cfg:52
msgid "arcane barrage"
msgstr ""
